bug.author: nattochaduke
bug.summary: Fix a link to pretrained model.
bug.description:
In the implementation of resnet, I found a wrong link to a pretrained model. The following link must be to resnet-50 pretrained model.
chainercv/chainercv/links/model/resnet/resnet.py
Line 112 in 6a0ccda
'resnet152_imagenet_trained_2018_11_26.npz',
I believe 'resnet50_imagenet_trained_2018_11_26.npz' should be the correct link, but I haven't checked yet.

comments.comment: Thank you for reporting the issue. I made PR for this <denchmark-link:https://github.com/chainer/chainercv/pull/751>#751</denchmark-link> .
